Not a stitch out of place
Sep 2024 • Solo
Not being a ‘fashion’ person I would have passed this by but a friend suggested I don’t and I’m really glad I went. This museum is exactly how I find museums most enjoyable: not overly crammed with items, information that is digestible so I’m not standing around reading for hours, interactive and a place where I can learn something new or leave with a fresh perspective. The Dior museum hit all those marks for me. I had a timed entry ticket and was glad I did, there was quite a line for folks without one. Even if you don’t stay to eat have a look in the cafe adjacent to the modest gift shop. Even the food is a work of art. In the cafe area there was also a photography exhibit of summer Olympians wearing Dior that I found creative and fresh.
